      "date": "2016-04-20 10:56:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> The patch itself looks good to me, but it doesn't explain why the\n > OSC device isn't setup when cl_ocd_udpate() is called. Could you\n > elaborate on this?\n\nThis issue occured on customer site. I was told they encountered client crash after add a new OST. And then MDS was rebooted since they mounted a client on MDS host. The MDS cannot mount after reboot. They were writeconf on MDS and mount it again. I was access this site to monitor them add the OST. The process is very smoothly. It hasn't any problem until now(Please refer to BGI-12). It can hardly to figure out what happen since the mountdata of failure point was wipe out when we know it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
